<div id="review_971432042" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/971432042" />
    <a title="Lisa" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/9757853-lisa"><img alt="Lisa" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1337902277p2/9757853.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/971432042?book_show_action=true">Jun 18, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lisa" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lisa" href="/user/show/9757853-lisa">Lisa</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer971432042" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15373490815645217160">I really wanted to stay on board with this character, Chris, and his adventures in the lands beyond death. The story is exciting, especially in the beginning, and has some gorgeous imagery (I love the &quot;delicate purl of surf&quot; Chris notices on the shore of the lake in Summerland). The story grows more tedious as it progresses and is so didactic that it gets boring and seems to go on for....well...yep, an eternity. Ann&apos;s helplessness and goodness is annoying, too, frankly. I was completely disguste</span>
  <span id="freeText15373490815645217160" style="display:none">I really wanted to stay on board with this character, Chris, and his adventures in the lands beyond death. The story is exciting, especially in the beginning, and has some gorgeous imagery (I love the "delicate purl of surf" Chris notices on the shore of the lake in Summerland). The story grows more tedious as it progresses and is so didactic that it gets boring and seems to go on for....well...yep, an eternity. Ann's helplessness and goodness is annoying, too, frankly. I was completely disgusted when I finally got to the climax, his 3-page speech to Ann, full of sexist crap like this: "Thank you for keeping my clothes clean, our homes clean, yourself clean." Ugh. Really?!? Wash your own clothes, you lazy bastard!</span>
  <a data-text-id="15373490815645217160" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


